	)
	(text "- I2C1 is sent to main board via header pins, but CSI also uses I2C1. Thus unusable if CSI is in use.\n- CSI connector and pinout inspiration comes from Raspberry Pi documentation. Specifically camera module 2 and 3 schematics.\n- 8 Pin hardware debug will most likely not be used, but cannot be disabled in CubeMX at least for FSBL. Might be possible to repurpose in code later.\n- Single wire debug is the primary method of programming/debugging the board using an external STLink programmer/debugger.\n- SWO will not be used on SWD port, as both pins are being used by FMC and SPI respectively"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 16.764 174.498 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.1588)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "53a437a2-b222-45a5-ace0-62e764267579")
	)
